title: Black Hill Circuit Race
description: Back for 2017 and possibly the final installment of the Black Hill Circuit Race. Let's kick off the MABRA Calendar with this Spring Classic held at Black Hill Regional Park in Boyds, Maryland, in upper Montgomery County,  just off I-270 south of Frederick and a nice bike ride from all points DC and Baltimore. Test out your early season legs with Team Bike Doctor.
course: Course: Course is a 1.5 mile on rolling terrain in clockwise direction. One short, small ring climb. Lots of twists and an uphill sprint finish, all within a great park setting. Yellow/centerline rule in effect. Riders on different laps may not work together. All riders will finish on the leaders last lap and that there is no free lap. Officials reserve the right to pull lap lapped riders. Great early season race venue!
registration:
Registration: Registration via http://www.bikereg.com. (no mail in registration). Online fee will apply. JUNIORS NEED WAIVERS SIGNED BY PARENT OR GUARDIAN. Online registration will close Thursday, March 23, 2017at 6:00 p.m.  Race day registration opens at 7:15 a.m. and closes 30 minutes before the start of posted start times.  There is a $10 late fee for day of registration

Entry Fee: $40 for all races. $20 for a second race.

One Day Licenses: One day licenses from USA Cycling will be available. Cost is $10 per day and are available during registration process on BikeReg and at registration (please use BikeReg!!)
notes:
Weather Policy: Race will be held rain or shine. Snow sticking on the course cancels. No Refunds. Check Team Bike Doctor website/facebook page and MABRA list-serve for information on race info day of race.

Contact Event: Robb Hampton, teambikedoctor@gmail.com

Additional Info:  www.teambikedoctor.org
directions: Google Maps is: Black Hill Regional Park,  Boyds, MD 20841 â€“  Please follow directions of course marshals. Be cautious and courteous at all times.

title: Route One Rampage
description: The Route One Rampage is MABRA's premier spring criterium. Come join the University of Maryland for a hard, technical race in beautiful downtown Hyattsville. The second edition of the Rampage brings in a race village complete with beer from Franklin's Brewery and food from local eateries.
course: The course runs clockwise and is a 4-corner circuit starting and finishing on the scenic US-1 while climbing through the vibrant 42nd Street neighborhood of Hyattsville's Arts District.
registration: The promoter reserves the right to eliminate any field that does not have at least 15 riders registered by March 18.
directions:
From I-95, continue onto I-95 N/495. Take exit for I-295, then take exit for US-50 W. Follow signs for MD-201
N. Follow 201, and turn left on Annapolis Road, then Right on Baltimore Avenue/Route 1, until reaching Hyattsville. 

Racers, spectators, and volunteers alike should park at Magruder Park or the Hyattsville Revenue Authority Parking Garauge. Free parking all day.
